---
Priority implementation order (business impact first):

1. C-1 — App is non-functional on real devices. Fix before any real user testing.
2. C-2 — Silent logout failure destroys session resilience.
3. C-3 — Security prerequisite for any production deployment.
4. H-4 — Brute-force risk on auth endpoints is exploitable from day one.
5. H-1 — Registration 500 is user-facing and intermittent (harder to diagnose).
6. H-2 — FX rate drift leads to incorrect pricing shown to customers.
7. H-3 — Performance degrades linearly; impacts all list views.
8. H-5 — API contract is broken for SEND orders from non-mobile clients.

